Rules for determining the size of a COMP-3 field (packed decimal)

Stored as Binary Coded Decimal (BCD). 2 Digits per byte with sign in the low nybble of the least significant bytr, no matter if the picture clause has a sign otr not.
Formula:
  Bytes = (n + 1)/2 rounded up
  
  COMP-3:     Bytes:
  S9(7)      4
  S9(5)V99   4
  S9(6)      4
  9(7)       4
  9(6)       4
